  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>Full Schedule</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Day 1 (Aug 4):</strong> Orientation · Dorm check‑in · Campus tour · Welcome mixer</li>
        <li><strong>Days 2–4 (Aug 5–7):</strong> Morning painting workshop · Midday figure drawing & critiques · Afternoon guest seminars & field trips · Evening open studio</li>
        <li><strong>Day 5 (Aug 8):</strong> Final presentations · Showcase · Closing ceremony · Check‑out</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Packing List</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Five days' worth of studio‑friendly clothing</li>
        <li>Twin‑XL bedding & toiletries · Closed‑toe shoes</li>
        <li>Water bottle & light snacks · Optional sketchbook or art tools</li>
        <li>Chargers, headphones, personal essentials</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Dorm Info</h2>
      <p>Housing is provided in <strong>Chouinard Hall</strong> on the CalArts campus. Rooms are double-occupancy and gender-inclusive options are available. Resident Assistants and CSSSA staff supervise 24/7. Shared bathrooms, Wi‑Fi, AC, and basic furnishings included.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Program FAQs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Is the program free?</strong> Yes! Tuition is waived—the only costs you cover are transportation and meals.</li>
        <li><strong>Are meals provided?</strong> Meals are not included but there are campus dining halls and nearby grocery options.</li>
        <li><strong>Who can attend?</strong> Students entering grades 9–12 in Fall 2025 or graduating Spring 2025.</li>
        <li><strong>Do I need to bring art supplies?</strong> Studio acrylic paints are provided; you can bring your own sketchbook or tools if you wish.</li>
        <li><strong>Questions?</strong> Email us at <a href="mailto:csssa.admissions@gmail.com">csssa.admissions@gmail.com</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
